-- Ferrovial in Talks to Acquire 3i’s Enterprise Unit, Times Says
-- B y   T h o m a s   B i e s h e u v e l
-- 2012-05-06T11:05:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-06/ferrovial-in-talks-to-buy-3i-s-enterprise-unit-times-reports.html
Ferrovial SA (FER)  is in talks to buy  3i
Group Plc (III) ’s Enterprise unit, a cleaning and waste collection
service, for 500 million pounds ($808 million), the Sunday Times
reported, without saying how it got the information.  Enterprise’s owner, 3i Group Plc, declined to comment, the
newspaper said.  A spokesman for Ferrovial declined to comment when
contacted by telephone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Thomas Biesheuvel in London at 
 tbiesheuvel@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
